Content: I wonder how Komodo want to increase blockchain speed without higher the 2mb blocksize or 59sec blocktime? how will this be done?

Content: I¬¥m just asking because I want to increase my KMD or DGB portfolio and I¬¥m not sure which one is better. I own both, like them both and DGB seems even faster as KMD and is also very secure in a different way

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: #dev-scalability

Author: KomodoWorld#8282
Content: @Hagen-von-Coinje  because KMD can use multiple chains instead of a single big one, the chains can do cross transfers with each other, they behave like one but with the load spread among many. Similar effect to sharding but without its problems, security issues, etc...

Author: KomodoWorld#8282
Content: https://komodoworld.blog/2018/07/15/scaling-via-multiple-chains/

Author: Hagen-von-Coinje#9555
Content: THX that sounds great. I really like these multiple chains concepts. What it does in the question of centralization is another question. DGB, as far as I know will using their singlechain concept, which might get in trouble in a few years, but they will work against that with bigger blocks. the decentralization might be better so?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: it seems that many chains is much more decentralized than a single big chain

Author: KomodoWorld#8282
Content: since users need only to run the blockchain they mostly use, it's more likely they will do so than if they had to download a single big chain

Author: Hagen-von-Coinje#9555
Content: thats the unknown for a non expert like me. Are many chains really more decentralized as one single chain? From the outside I would say that this "ecosystem" must be "managed" or be "controlled" by someone

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: it does rely on being notarized for the cross chain to work. other than that everyting is independent

Author: Hagen-von-Coinje#9555
Content: hope everything works out well with these architectures,  I¬¥m invested in KMD, Icon, AELF, Aeon and Elastos to diversify a bit in the hope that everyone will succeed in their way.
